  <h2>About me</h2>
  <p>
    Hands-on DevRel engineer: I research features, issues, and tools, I build
    working demos, write the docs and tutorials that explain them, and get in
    front of developers: on camera, in live workshops, in short- and long-form
    video, and in writing. Two decades of technical background (development,
    sysadmin, infrastructure, training) plus 10+ years producing technical
    content in native-level English and Spanish. I care about one metric above
    all: how fast a developer gets from "this looks interesting" to "I grok it
    (deeply understand it) and I'm using it effectively."
  </p>

  <h2>Experience</h2>

  <h3>
    Developer Relations / Technical Content Creator — DonWeb Cloud &amp; IaaS
  </h3>
  <p class="meta">DonWeb Cloud · Argentina/remote · 2024–2025</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Created the developer-facing content program for DonWeb's Cloud &amp; IaaS
      products, reporting to the division's Marketing Manager and Product Owner
      (VP of Product): tutorials, guides, video, and demos covering VPS, Linux,
      Docker, CI/CD with GitHub Actions, DNS/SSL, CMS platforms, and app
      deployment.
    </li>
    <li>
      Designed and delivered live programming and DevOps workshops (2x/month,
      300+ sign-ups, 150+ live attendance).
    </li>
    <li>
      Sustained a video cadence of <strong
        >3 short-form videos per week plus one in-depth long-form video per
        month</strong
      > across social channels (in collaboration with a video editor/brand designer).
    </li>
    <li>
      Built and tested every environment, command, and config shipped in content
      — and reviewed production VPS images, scripts, and configuration examples
      for correctness and reproducibility.
    </li>
    <li>
      Translated complex infrastructure workflows into onboarding paths for
      developers new to cloud tooling.
    </li>
    <li>
      Produced content and demos for product launches in other divisions
      (EnvialoSimple, Mi Cuenta) and internal training for L1 support staff.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>
    Freelance Technical Content, Translation &amp; Review — Fiverr / Upwork /
    Direct
  </h3>
  <p class="meta">
    Self-employed · 2017–present · Top Seller status, 2,500+ completed projects,
    96% repeat clients
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Produced and reviewed developer-facing content for international clients:
      API documentation, tutorials, training guides, white papers, and
      localization for US, UK, EU, and Australian tech companies.
    </li>
    <li>
      Built a Top Seller reputation on quality and reliability at high volume —
      1,500+ positive reviews.
    </li>
    <li>
      English↔Spanish technical translation at native level across software,
      cybersecurity, networking, and developer education.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Content Creator — matiasbaldanza @ Twitch</h3>
  <p class="meta">Twitch/YouTube · 2022–present</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Streamed daily learn-in-public sessions on front-end development (React,
      Next.js) from 2022–2024, averaging <strong>100 concurrent viewers</strong> with
      peaks of 180–200 — comfortable on camera, live-coding, unscripted Q&amp;A.
    </li>
    <li>
      Currently active on X and GitHub, building and sharing developer tooling
      experiments: AI coding agents (Claude Code, MCP servers), self-hosted
      infra, RAG/evals workflows.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Earlier career — IT Specialist / Sysadmin / Instructor</h3>
  <p class="meta">Various employers · 1998–2017</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      13 years in networking, support, incident response, and systems
      administration (Generación WiFi S.A. and others), head of support for a
      local ISP and technical services company, outsourced to banks and
      enterprises for deployments and incident response. Wrote the
      documentation, checklists, and FAQs, trained technical staff.
    </li>
    <li>
      Instructor and Academic Coordinator at a training facility: designed and
      taught technical courses for corporate clients and an MCSE/MCP training
      center.
    </li>
  </ul>

